  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 8e2e1bb8d9ac9f548824584e9c1df4be, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::JumblerLogic
  quotes:
  - We can only see a short distance ahead, but we can see plenty there that needs
    to be done.
  - That brain of mine is something more than merely mortal; as time will show.
  - The most dangerous phrase in the language is, 'We've always done it this way'.
  - Hope and curiosity about the future seemed better than guarantees
  - In mathematics you don't understand things. You just get used to them.
  - I like to learn. That's an art and a science.
  - We're having an information explosion, and it's certainly obvious that information
    is of no use unless it's available
  - Logic is the foundation of the certainty of all the knowledge we acquire.
  - The world would be a better place if more engineers, like me, hated technology
  - I'll bet you don't have a computer in your living room.
  person:
  - Alan Turing
  - Ada Lovelace
  - Grace Hopper
  - Hedy Lamarr
  - John von Neumann
  - Katherin Johnson
  - Sister Mary Kenneth Keller
  - Leonhard Euler
  - Radia Perlman
  - Mary Allen Wilkes
  unjumbled: 
  numQuote: 10
  author: 
  jumbled: 
  targetMaxChar: 22
